text:
An 18-year-old boy was stabbed and set on fire in a gruesome attack in a Bronx hallway that began with an argument.

He was stabbed several times before his assailant poured accelerant on him and lit him ablaze, cops said, finding him with extensive burns.

text:
OPINION | Canceling rent won’t solve housing woes

Landlords won’t survive months of rent famine, and bankruptcies in rental housing will not help the housing crisis that we've wrestled with for decades. 

Attorney Ethan Blevins writes @ethanwb @ethanwb

name: NYDailyNews
text:
Scientists in San Francisco say they've invented a nasal spray that should be able to stop coronavirus before it gains entry into the cells lining lungs and airways.

The spray could be an important stopgap until vaccines become available.
